<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="37" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,151,338]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,338,271,297]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is found in arid thorn forest and the other species are known from moist forest, thus the name “ 
<taxonomicName box="[334,428,312,337]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthochilum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xericum">
<emphasis box="[334,428,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">xericum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” indicates the habitat preference for this particular species.
</paragraph>
